        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued May 16 at 7:32PM EDT until May 16 at 8:00PM EDT by NWS Binghamton NY</headline>
        <description>At 731 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Bridgewater, or
12 miles south of New Hartford, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Paris, Brookfield, Waterville, Richfield Springs, West Winfield,
Oriskany Falls, Bridgewater, Clayville, Madison, and Poolville.

This storm knocked down a couple trees in the Hamilton area.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
